lsfStaticTable.name: lsfStaticTable
lsfStaticTable.description: A table which corresponds to information displayed by the lshosts command.

lsfStaticEntry.name: lsfStaticEntry
lsfStaticEntry.description: One instance (row) of host information. It is indexed by the host's IP address in order to provide a deterministic way of accessing a specific host's configuration information.

lsfStaticIpIndex.name: lsfStaticIpIndex
lsfStaticIpIndex.description: IP address of this host as known by LSF.

lsfHostName.name: lsfHostName
lsfHostName.description: Host name for this host as known by LSF.

lsfType.name: lsfType
lsfType.description: Type of this host. Available host types are defined in the lsf.shared file, and can be displayed using the lsinfo command.

lsfModel.name: lsfModel
lsfModel.description: Model of this host. Available host models are defined in the lsf.shared file, and can be displayed using the lsinfo command.

lsfCPUFactor.name: lsfCPUFactor
lsfCPUFactor.description: A relative measure of this host's CPU speed. It is normally represented as a floating point number, and thus has been scaled by 100 for representation in the SNMP.

lsfNumCPU.name: lsfNumCPU
lsfNumCPU.description: Number of CPUs in this host.

lsfMaxMemory.name: lsfMaxMemory
lsfMaxMemory.description: The configured amount of RAM in this host, in megabytes.

lsfMaxSwap.name: lsfMaxSwap
lsfMaxSwap.description: The configured amount of physical swap space on this host, in megabytes.

lsfMaxTempSpace.name: lsfMaxTempSpace
lsfMaxTempSpace.description: The size of the temporary file space on this machine. Typically this corresponds to /tmp, but can be overridden in LSF configuration files by the LSF_TMPDIR environment variable.

lsfExecutionPriority.name: lsfExecutionPriority
lsfExecutionPriority.description: The execution priority, or nice level, of processes spawned by the RES on this host.

lsfIsServer.name: lsfIsServer
lsfIsServer.description: true if this host will accept and run remote processes, and false if it won't.

lsfHostResources.name: lsfHostResources
lsfHostResources.description: A string containing the boolean resources applied to this host. Available boolean resources can be displayed using the lsinfo command.

lsfDynamicTable.name: lsfDynamicTable
lsfDynamicTable.description: A table which corresponds to information displayed by the lsload command.

lsfDynamicEntry.name: lsfDynamicEntry
lsfDynamicEntry.description: One instance (row) of host information. It is indexed by the host's IP address in order to provide a deterministic way of accessing a specific host's load information.

lsfDynamicIpIndex.name: lsfDynamicIpIndex
lsfDynamicIpIndex.description: IP address of this host as known by LSF.

lsfHostStatus.name: lsfHostStatus
lsfHostStatus.description: The operating status of LSF on this host. The host can be locked from a management entity by setting this variable to lockU(4). If the host status is lockW(5), the status will become lockUW(6). The management entity can also unlock a host by attempting to set it to ok(1).

lsfFifteenSecondRunQueue.name: lsfFifteenSecondRunQueue
lsfFifteenSecondRunQueue.description: The 15 second run queue length on this host. This value is a float which is scaled by 100 to format it as an integer.

lsfOneMinuteRunQueue.name: lsfOneMinuteRunQueue
lsfOneMinuteRunQueue.description: The 1 minute run queue length on this host. This value is a float which is scaled by 100 to format it as an integer.

lsfFifteenMinuteRunQueue.name: lsfFifteenMinuteRunQueue
lsfFifteenMinuteRunQueue.description: The 15 minute run queue length on this host. This value is a float which is scaled by 100 to format it as an integer.

lsfCPUUtilization.name: lsfCPUUtilization
lsfCPUUtilization.description: A percentage of how much CPU time is spent processing system and user processes. A high utilization means that a host's CPU is kept busy.

lsfPagingRate.name: lsfPagingRate
lsfPagingRate.description: A measure of page-in and page-out requests on this host over the lim sample interval. Since it is a floating point number in LSF, it is scaled by 100 to represent it as an INTEGER.

lsfIoRate.name: lsfIoRate
lsfIoRate.description: A measure of number of disk operations on this host over the last lim sample interval.

lsfLoginSessions.name: lsfLoginSessions
lsfLoginSessions.description: The number of login sessions on this host.

lsfIdleTime.name: lsfIdleTime
lsfIdleTime.description: The number of seconds for which all interactive login sessions have been idle on this host.

lsfFreeMemory.name: lsfFreeMemory
lsfFreeMemory.description: The amount of free real memory on this host, in megabytes.

lsfFreeSwap.name: lsfFreeSwap
lsfFreeSwap.description: The amount of free physical swap on this host, in megabytes.

lsfFreeTempSpace.name: lsfFreeTempSpace
lsfFreeTempSpace.description: The amount of free space in the temporary filesystem, in megabytes. This is typically /tmp, but can be overridden in the LSF configuration files using the LSF_TMPDIR environment variable.

lsfNumericTable.name: lsfNumericTable
lsfNumericTable.description: A table which describes numeric type external indices and shared resources defined for a cluster.

lsfNumericEntry.name: lsfNumericEntry
lsfNumericEntry.description: One instance of resource information. It is indexed by two entries: host IpAddress and a resource index which is generated by the agent by sorting a list of resource names, and numbering the resource names in ascending alphabetical order.

lsfNumericIndex.name: lsfNumericIndex
lsfNumericIndex.description: A number generated by the agent to uniquely identify this resource name.

lsfNumericIP.name: lsfNumericIP
lsfNumericIP.description: The IP address corresponding to the location of this resource.

lsfNumericLocation.name: lsfNumericLocation
lsfNumericLocation.description: The host on which this resource is located.

lsfNumericOrder.name: lsfNumericOrder
lsfNumericOrder.description: Indicates the direction which denotes higher load. If a resource is ascending, the load is higher when the resource is higher (e.g. incoming packets). If the resource is descending, the load is higher when the resource is lower (e.g. space on a temporary filesystem).

lsfNumericValue.name: lsfNumericValue
lsfNumericValue.description: The current value of this resource. Note that floating point values will be scaled by 100 before being returned.

lsbHostTable.name: lsbHostTable
lsbHostTable.description: A table which provides the same information as the bhosts command without any arguments.

lsbHostEntry.name: lsbHostEntry
lsbHostEntry.description: One instance of batch host information. It is indexed by the host's IP address.

lsbHostStatus.name: lsbHostStatus
lsbHostStatus.description: Current status of this host. Only when a host is in ok status can batch jobs be dispatched to it. An SNMP management entity can close hosts by setting this variable to closed(4), and can reopen hosts by setting this variable to ok(1).

lsbHostUserJobLimit.name: lsbHostUserJobLimit
lsbHostUserJobLimit.description: Maximum batch job slots that the host can provide per user.

lsbHostMaximumJobs.name: lsbHostMaximumJobs
lsbHostMaximumJobs.description: Maximum number of job slots that the host can provide in total.

lsbHostNumberOfJobs.name: lsbHostNumberOfJobs
lsbHostNumberOfJobs.description: Number of job slots used by jobs started on this host.

lsbHostRunningJobs.name: lsbHostRunningJobs
lsbHostRunningJobs.description: Number of job slots used by jobs running on this host.

lsbSystemSuspendedJobs.name: lsbSystemSuspendedJobs
lsbSystemSuspendedJobs.description: Number of job slots used by jobs suspended by LSF on the host.

lsbUserSuspendedJobs.name: lsbUserSuspendedJobs
lsbUserSuspendedJobs.description: Number of job slots used by jobs suspended by the job owner or an LSF administrator

lsbHostReservedJobSlots.name: lsbHostReservedJobSlots
lsbHostReservedJobSlots.description: Number of job slots used by pending jobs which have job slots reserved on the host.

lsbQueueTable.name: lsbQueueTable
lsbQueueTable.description: A table which provides the same information as the bqueues command without any arguments.

lsbQueueEntry.name: lsbQueueEntry
lsbQueueEntry.description: One instance of batch queue information. The index field is generated by the agent by sorting the list of queues, and numbering the queue names in ascending alphabetical order.

lsbQueueIndex.name: lsbQueueIndex
lsbQueueIndex.description: A number generated by the agent to uniquely identify this queue.

lsbQueuePriority.name: lsbQueuePriority
lsbQueuePriority.description: The priority of the queue. It determines the order in which job queues are searched for jobs to dispatch. Queues with higher priorities are searched first.

lsbQueueIsOpen.name: lsbQueueIsOpen
lsbQueueIsOpen.description: A flag telling whether the queue is open to accept jobs submitted to it, or whether it is closed so that it will not accept jobs. The management entity can set this variable to open(1) or closed(2) to change the submission status of this queue.

lsbQueueIsActive.name: lsbQueueIsActive
lsbQueueIsActive.description: A flag telling whether the queue is active (dispatching jobs to run), or whether it is inactive so that jobs are not being dispatched. The management entity can set this variable to active(1) or inactive(2) to change the dispatching status of this queue.

lsbQueueMaximumJobs.name: lsbQueueMaximumJobs
lsbQueueMaximumJobs.description: The maximum number of job slots which can be used by jobs from this queue.

lsbQueueUserJobLimit.name: lsbQueueUserJobLimit
lsbQueueUserJobLimit.description: The maximum number of job slots a user can use for his/her jobs in this queue.

lsbQueueProcessorJobLimit.name: lsbQueueProcessorJobLimit
lsbQueueProcessorJobLimit.description: The maximum number of job slots which a processor can process from this queue. This limit controls the number of jobs sent to each host. The limit is configured per processor so that a multiprocessor host is automatically allowed to run more jobs.

lsbQueueHostJobLimit.name: lsbQueueHostJobLimit
lsbQueueHostJobLimit.description: The maximum number of job slots which a host can process from this queue. This limit controls the number of jobs sent to each host, regardless of whether a host is a uniprocessor or a multiprocessor.

lsbQueueNumberOfJobs.name: lsbQueueNumberOfJobs
lsbQueueNumberOfJobs.description: The total number of job slots which jobs in this queue are currently holding.

lsbQueuePendingJobs.name: lsbQueuePendingJobs
lsbQueuePendingJobs.description: The number of pending job slots in this queue.

lsbQueueRunningJobs.name: lsbQueueRunningJobs
lsbQueueRunningJobs.description: The number of running job slots in this queue.

lsbQueueSystemSuspendedJobs.name: lsbQueueSystemSuspendedJobs
lsbQueueSystemSuspendedJobs.description: The number of job slots suspended by the system in this queue.

lsbQueueUserSuspendedJobs.name: lsbQueueUserSuspendedJobs
lsbQueueUserSuspendedJobs.description: The number of job slots suspended by the user in this queue.

lsbJobTable.name: lsbJobTable
lsbJobTable.description: A table which provides the same information as the bjobs -r -u all command, and the resource usage of each running job.

lsbJobEntry.name: lsbJobEntry
lsbJobEntry.description: An instance of a running job. The entries are indexed by jobID, since it uniquely identifies running jobs in the batch system.

lsbJobID.name: lsbJobID
lsbJobID.description: The number which uniquely identifies this job in the batch system.

lsbJobName.name: lsbJobName
lsbJobName.description: The job name assigned by the user, or the command string assigned by default.

lsbJobUser.name: lsbJobUser
lsbJobUser.description: The user who submitted the job.

lsbJobQueue.name: lsbJobQueue
lsbJobQueue.description: The name of the queue to which the job belongs.

lsbJobStatus.name: lsbJobStatus
lsbJobStatus.description: The current status of the job.

lsbJobSubmissionHost.name: lsbJobSubmissionHost
lsbJobSubmissionHost.description: The name of the host from which the job was submitted.

lsbJobExecutionHost.name: lsbJobExecutionHost
lsbJobExecutionHost.description: The name of one or more hosts on which the job is executing. If the field is empty, the job has not been dispatched yet. If the execution host for a job has been removed from the configuration, this will be displayed as lost_and_found.

lsbJobSubmitTime.name: lsbJobSubmitTime
lsbJobSubmitTime.description: The submission time of the job.

lsbJobProcessGroupIds.name: lsbJobProcessGroupIds
lsbJobProcessGroupIds.description: A space delimited list of process group ids which make up this job.

lsbJobProcessIds.name: lsbJobProcessIds
lsbJobProcessIds.description: A space delimited list of process ids which make up this job.

lsbJobCpuUsage.name: lsbJobCpuUsage
lsbJobCpuUsage.description: The cumulative total CPU time in seconds of all processes in a job.

lsbJobMemoryUsage.name: lsbJobMemoryUsage
lsbJobMemoryUsage.description: The total resident memory usage in KBytes of all the processes in a job.

lsbJobVirtualMemoryUsage.name: lsbJobVirtualMemoryUsage
lsbJobVirtualMemoryUsage.description: The total virtual memory usage in KBytes of all the processes in a job.

lsfLimDown.name: lsfLimDown
lsfLimDown.description: This trap is sent when the lim on a host goes down. The variable points to the status of the host on which the lim went down.

lsfResDown.name: lsfResDown
lsfResDown.description: This trap is sent when the res on a host goes down. The variable points to the status of the host on which the res went down.

lsfSbdDown.name: lsfSbdDown
lsfSbdDown.description: This trap is sent when the sbatchd on a host goes down. The variable points to the status of the batch host on which the sbatchd went down.

lsfHostUnlicensed.name: lsfHostUnlicensed
lsfHostUnlicensed.description: This trap is sent when a host in the cluster becomes unlicensed.

lsfMasterElect.name: lsfMasterElect
lsfMasterElect.description: This trap is sent to announce which host has won the master election.

lsfMbdUp.name: lsfMbdUp
lsfMbdUp.description: This trap is sent when an mbatchd comes up on a host, has done its initialization and replay, and is ready to start accepting and scheduling jobs.

lsfMbdDown.name: lsfMbdDown
lsfMbdDown.description: This trap is sent if the mbatchd goes down in the cluster. It could be sent by mbatchd itself, or could be sent by some other agent which detects the condition.

lsfMbdReconfig.name: lsfMbdReconfig
lsfMbdReconfig.description: This trap is sent by the mbatchd when it is going to reconfigure itself.

lsfWorkdirFull.name: lsfWorkdirFull
lsfWorkdirFull.description: This trap is sent if the mbatchd cannot write to the LSB_SHAREDIR because it is full.
